  "texts": [
    "To incorporate causality, Frye et al. [41] introduced the framework of Asymmetric Shapley values (ASVs), which is an extension of the traditional Shapley values that relax symmetry axiom, which can be applied to various ML models without requiring a complete causal graph, even with limited knowledge of causal relationships.",
    "Heskes et al. [42] proposed causal Shapley value framework, which utilizes Pearl's do-calculus [43] to overcome the assumption of independence and demonstrates how to derive these causal Shapley values for general causal graphs without sacrificing any desirable properties.",
    "This approach enables a more accurate and meaningful attribution of the overall effects of features on predictions.",
    "To establish a unified framework capturing direct and indirect effects among variables with causal relationships, Wang et al. [44] proposed Shapley Flow, which takes [42] marginal Wang et al.",
    "[44] marginalWe ranked the algorithms based on Shapley value, Owen value, and causal Shapley value."
  ]
}